This paper discusses the use of big data analytics for proactive content caching in 5G wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of edge/cloud computing, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of machine learning for analysis could also place this paper under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or cryptography and security (cs.CR) if the focus is on securing the data being analyzed. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of large amounts of data, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
